Direct Known Subclasses:
ExtendedSet
public class ForwardingFluentSet<E>
extends AbstractEnumerable<E>
implements FluentSet<E>

Wraps around any Set implementation, and delegates all set methods to this delegateSet .

array

public <T> T[] array(Class<T> clazz)
Description copied from interface: FluentSet
Similar to the method toArray, but receives no args and is type safe. Also, the returned array is just a copy. Note that the class is necessary, as Generics by themselves cannot solve this problem alone. For more info: http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/java/library/j-jtp01255.html

Specified by:
array in interface ExtendedCollection<E>
Specified by:
array in interface FluentSet<E>
Returns:
A copy of the set as an array.

symmetricDifference

public FluentSet<E> symmetricDifference(Iterable<? extends E> iterable)
Description copied from interface: FluentSet
Returns a new Fluent Set with the symmetric difference of this and the set of elements from the iterable. That is: the union of this and iterable minus the intersection of this and iterable. In other words: a set with what is exclusive to this and the set of elements of iterable.

Specified by:
symmetricDifference in interface FluentSet<E>
